Thousands of mourners poured into the city of Moncton on Monday to honor three Royal Canadian Mounted Police (RCMP) officers killed in last week's shooting spree.

Prior to the funeral for Constables Dave Ross, Douglas Larche and Fabrice Gevaudan, RCMP officers marched through Moncton in a funeral procession. Each officer's casket was driven through the procession in a hearse.

